# Component Folder Structure

- Each component must live in its own folder named after the component.
- Every component folder must contain `index.tsx` as the component entry file.
- Move styles into a dedicated styles file (for example `styles.ts`, `styles.module.css`, or `styles.css`).
- Put constants in `consts.ts`.
- Put helper functions in `utils.ts`.
- Keep component-specific types in `types.ts` when needed.
- Keep related tests next to the component (`index.test.tsx`).

## Target shape

```text
ComponentName/
  index.tsx
  styles.module.css
  consts.ts
  index.test.tsx
```
